				<p><p>First, let's consider what actuator you need to physically push a button. One straight forward solution is to use a RC-Servo motor. An RC-Servo motor is a high torque (DC motor with gearbox) actuator which can be instructed to rotate at a specific angle. It is controlled through a PWM signal. So you need to figure out the duty cycle of the PWM signal to do the desired movement and push the button you want.</p>

<p>Secondly we need a controller that:</p>

<ul>
<li>is able to generate a PWM signal</li>
<li>communicate through the Internet</li>
</ul>

<p>First thing that comes to my mind is to use a Raspberry Pi. Of course it is a huge overkill to use it just for pushing a button but in the process you will learn a lot of interesting things about setting up Raspberry Pi. You can setup a minimal web-server using python in less that 5 minutes.
Arduino with an Ethernet shield as DaemonMaker suggested is also a great setup.</p>
</p><br>
